And you could even say, you're more culpable for this.

19:57.803 --> 20:04.510
You literally just watched me take the lives of your two brothers for doing the same thing in a different way.

20:05.030 --> 20:09.394
So get it right, get to the details, perform for me and do it this way.

20:09.915 --> 20:11.697
If that's really what's going on.

20:12.618 --> 20:15.761
But this isn't, I don't think what's truly happening here.

20:16.802 --> 20:21.106
And what you're about to see is gonna show you something about the heart of God

20:21.250 --> 20:24.314
in the entire nature of the Old Testament law.

20:24.595 --> 20:27.539
Look at Aaron's response in verse 19.

20:29.361 --> 20:38.314
Aaron spoke to Moses, behold, this very day they presented their sin offering and their burnt offering before the Lord.

20:39.015 --> 20:49.810
When things like these happened to me, if I had eaten a sin offering today, would it have been good in the sight of our Lord?

20:50.594 --> 20:52.056
Notice who speaks here, by the way.

20:52.337 --> 20:54.800
Moses has frustrated at the two remaining sons.

20:54.981 --> 20:56.864
LEAs are in Itsmar, but it's Aaron now.

20:57.264 --> 20:59.548
He's not passive, he's the one that speaks.

21:00.049 --> 21:02.412
And he defends his two oldest sons.

21:02.993 --> 21:08.181
This very day, they presented their sin offering and their burn offering, job done.

21:08.221 --> 21:12.247
They did what they were required to do.

21:12.708 --> 21:13.850
Meaning they did their job.

21:13.890 --> 21:16.113
They made atonement for the sin of the people.

21:16.173 --> 21:17.796
That is complete.

21:18.317 --> 21:19.218
However,

21:19.746 --> 21:22.949
They stopped short of eating the sacrifice.

21:23.690 --> 21:25.753
What's Aaron's explanation?

21:26.053 --> 21:28.395
Or what question does he pose?

21:28.415 --> 21:28.916
Do you see it?

21:29.677 --> 21:39.948
When things like these happen to me, if I had eaten the offering today, the sin offering today, would it have been good in the sight of our Lord?

21:40.488 --> 21:42.811
What are things like these?

21:43.251 --> 21:44.393
What is he referring to?

21:44.413 --> 21:46.996
He said, I just watched my sons die.

21:47.716 --> 21:49.298
I'm racked over this.

21:49.666 --> 21:53.171
They literally were just consumed in a fire by God 15 minutes ago.

21:53.191 --> 21:58.778
Is the right next step for me now to go through this process?

21:59.259 --> 22:04.646
And again, he's saying, I'm not in disagreement with what God has done, but I'm grieving what has happened.

22:05.127 --> 22:08.632
And he's saying, Moses, I have two options at this point in the juncture, at this point of the game.

22:08.832 --> 22:09.753
There's a fork in the road.

22:10.254 --> 22:12.677
I can either go through the motions.

22:13.478 --> 22:14.900
I can fake it all externally.

22:15.200 --> 22:17.143
I can check the boxes in a lot of ways.

22:17.203 --> 22:19.346
By the way, that would be the easier thing to do.

22:19.842 --> 22:24.407
Or I can ask the question, what does God desire of me right now?

22:25.509 --> 22:31.095
And to not fake it on the outside when my inside is not congruent with what's going on.

22:31.936 --> 22:38.144
And think about for a moment the risk of asking this question right now.

22:39.505 --> 22:46.674
His two other sons lives hang in the balance of Aaron thinking he knows the right answer to this question.

22:47.010 --> 22:50.474
that he knows the heart and mind of God in this matter.

22:51.015 --> 22:53.898
He's saying, I don't think this is what the Lord wants.

22:54.619 --> 23:02.208
I know the rule, but today in my grief, Moses eating would have been performative, not faithful.

23:03.089 --> 23:04.951
He's saying, this wasn't accidental.

23:05.471 --> 23:06.913
My sons didn't screw up.

23:07.834 --> 23:12.880
We intentionally had the entire sacrifice consumed on that altar.

23:13.280 --> 23:14.642
That was not an accident.

23:14.978 --> 23:29.378
We did that because my heart, my son's heart are not in a place to respond that way in worship in a true, genuine, joyful way that is what God would desire in that moment.

23:29.398 --> 23:33.884
And what Aaron is recognizing is God desires truth in my inward being.

23:33.964 --> 23:36.949
At least that's what he's supposing to be true.

23:37.670 --> 23:41.355
So the million dollar question in this chapter is, is he right?

23:42.396 --> 23:43.698
Does Moses agree?

23:43.938 --> 23:46.822
And more importantly, does God agree?

23:47.683 --> 23:50.566
Look at verse 20 where the text concludes.

23:51.587 --> 23:56.473
When Moses heard that, it seemed good in his sight.

23:57.875 --> 24:00.999
Moses stops and he ponders.

24:02.401 --> 24:03.823
He listens to Aaron's response.

24:04.784 --> 24:06.526
Aaron had asked the question, is this good?

24:07.387 --> 24:09.470
Would this please God in this moment?

24:10.331 --> 24:13.074
And Moses says, you're right.

24:14.242 --> 24:15.905
That's exactly what would please God.

24:16.426 --> 24:18.650
For you not to participate in that.

24:19.351 --> 24:25.081
For you to not allow your hands and your heart to be disconnected.

24:25.642 --> 24:27.725
God does not want you to fake it on the outside.

24:27.765 --> 24:28.747
Yes, you did your job.

24:28.787 --> 24:29.929
You completed your task.

24:30.029 --> 24:32.894
The sins of the people have been atoned for.

24:33.616 --> 24:39.666
And Moses agrees, and more importantly, speaking on behalf of God, God agrees with this as well.

24:40.002 --> 24:50.536
Aaron knew that the mere mechanical act of observing the ritual would not have pleased God for the Lord looks at the heart and wants obedience not sacrifice.

24:51.257 --> 25:00.570
And even though Aaron acted out of an inner sense of behavior that honored God, he was technically in violation of God's law.

25:00.970 --> 25:03.694
Y'all this is crazy in Old Testament days.

25:04.215 --> 25:06.738
And Aaron again is asking a much deeper question

25:07.010 --> 25:08.391
Does God want me to fake it?

25:08.411 --> 25:10.694
Does He want me to check the box and move on?

25:10.974 --> 25:17.080
What Aaron is supposing, is there something so much greater about the character and nature of God?

25:17.501 --> 25:22.726
He believes in that moment God wants those things together, congruent in his life in an hours.

25:23.147 --> 25:30.154
That God is absolutely concerned about us walking in obedience, but not heartless obedience.

25:31.035 --> 25:34.098
And by the way, this idea is not unique here.

25:34.402 --> 25:37.527
It is all over your Bible from literally beginning to end.

25:38.248 --> 25:44.058
Think about Genesis chapter four, the two sons of Adam and Eve, Cain and Abel.

25:44.098 --> 25:46.321
They both bring sacrifices before the Lord.

25:46.722 --> 25:49.707
And it says that God accepts one and rejects the other.

25:50.227 --> 25:53.913
We're told very clearly it has nothing to do with the object that they bring.

25:54.134 --> 25:58.761
Both sacrifices were on the okay list, so to speak, of things that honor God.

25:59.122 --> 26:01.746
And both boys brought what they had.

26:01.826 --> 26:06.552
One brought from the fruit of the ground, because he was a farmer, the other brought an animal, because that's what he did.

26:07.072 --> 26:09.415
And it says that God accepted one and rejected the other.

26:10.096 --> 26:20.208
One it says is the leftovers, the rejects, the things that after I've taken everything from me, then I will give to God, because one of the boys, that is how they viewed God.

26:20.929 --> 26:26.616
And the other boy says, gave his first and gave his best, because that's how he viewed God.

26:27.076 --> 26:28.658
And God says, I accept that.

26:28.962 --> 26:30.965
because you understand who I am in your life.

26:31.365 --> 26:37.113
That attitude, though, where I'm last or I'm least and I get your leftovers, that's not what I want.

26:37.133 --> 26:48.529
To the very last chapter, by the way, the last book of our Bible in Malachi, where Malachi is rebuking the people for the blind and sick and lame animals that they were offering to God.

26:48.850 --> 26:51.754
He says, yeah, you're technically checking all the boxes.

26:52.175 --> 26:57.522
You're giving the correct sacrifice that God asked for, but your hearts are jacked.

26:57.890 --> 27:07.385
He says to them in Malachi one verse nine, but how will you not entreat God's favor that he would be gracious to us with such an offering on your part?

27:07.906 --> 27:10.089
Will he receive any of you kindly?

27:10.570 --> 27:11.591
Says the Lord of hosts.

27:11.932 --> 27:20.666
He says, oh, that there were one among you that would shut the gates that you might not uselessly kindle fire on my altar.

27:21.387 --> 27:23.570
I am not pleased with you.

27:23.874 --> 27:25.396
says the Lord of hosts.

27:25.416 --> 27:27.078
Nor will I accept an offering from you.

27:27.099 --> 27:27.439
Wait, wait, wait.

27:27.800 --> 27:29.402
So God, we gave all the right offerings.

27:29.422 --> 27:32.907
We checked all the right boxes because we didn't do it with the right heart posture.

27:33.187 --> 27:34.349
You say you won't accept them.

27:34.369 --> 27:35.651
God says, absolutely.

27:36.492 --> 27:37.854
Now you're beginning to understand.

27:38.775 --> 27:44.863
God says, I would prefer that you would actually take a padlock and shut the gates and lock the tabernacle down.

27:45.504 --> 27:46.706
Lock the temple down.

27:46.978 --> 27:55.989
before you would continue to offer these type of heartless, meaningless, religious, rote sacrifices to me.

27:56.370 --> 27:57.431
That's not what I want.

27:57.872 --> 27:58.893
That's not what I desire.

27:58.913 --> 28:05.301
In fact, Malachi says, you wouldn't even offer that to a human governor, much less the God of the universe.

28:05.321 --> 28:07.203
So stop giving me your scraps.

28:07.243 --> 28:09.346
That is not what I desire of you.

28:10.167 --> 28:15.634
And by the way, that theme is one that can be found in the Old Testament, but in the New Testament as well.

28:16.194 --> 28:36.319
When Jesus is interacting with the religious leaders of the day, the Pharisees who were famous for having this beautiful external facade and then inwardly being a hot mess, God said to them, Jesus said to them, but do they do all their deeds to be noticed by men for they broaden their phylacteries and they lengthen the tassels on their garments?

28:36.339 --> 28:38.962
They do all this religious external show.

28:39.170 --> 28:42.034
But he says, whoa, do you scribes and Pharisees you hypocrites?

28:42.595 --> 28:49.204
For you clean the outside of the cup and the dish, but the inside they are full of robbery and self-indulgence.

28:49.224 --> 28:51.667
Whoa, do you scribes and Pharisees hypocrites?

28:52.288 --> 29:02.542
You who are like whitewashed tombs, which on the outside appear beautiful, but inside they are full of dead men's bones and uncleanliness.

29:02.662 --> 29:05.266
On the outside, y'all look pristine.

29:05.666 --> 29:08.048
but your hearts are rotten to the core.

29:08.389 --> 29:17.457
And what's worse is that you think that God is honored in that because you're checking all the boxes.

29:18.778 --> 29:21.421
You think that's what he desires of you.

29:22.262 --> 29:25.304
So it begs the question, what has God after?

29:26.345 --> 29:28.808
What has God always been after?

29:29.568 --> 29:35.474
We're told in Hosea six verse six, for I desire steadfast love

29:36.034 --> 29:41.520
and not sacrifice the knowledge of God rather than burn offerings.

29:41.540 --> 29:49.928
God says, I want heart and hands connected, but the heart comes first because the heart is what drives that posture.

29:50.469 --> 29:54.834
Everything that happens externally comes from what's happening internally.

29:55.674 --> 29:57.897
Now, there's a caution we need to all be aware of here.

29:57.917 --> 30:02.962
This is not giving us permission to say, hey, God, when my heart's not in it, I can just be disobedient.

30:03.170 --> 30:08.480
I don't get to come home from work today and tell my wife, hey, I'm not going to empty the trash because honey, my heart's just not there.

30:09.562 --> 30:10.804
And God doesn't want me to perform.

30:10.864 --> 30:13.549
He doesn't want me to take out the trash if I'm not feeling it in here.

30:14.010 --> 30:15.233
That's a step too far.

30:15.253 --> 30:16.956
I don't think that's what this text is teaching.

30:17.236 --> 30:21.104
But it is saying that those things need to be congruent.

30:21.965 --> 30:22.386
Aaron.

30:22.658 --> 30:47.922
Eleazar it tomorrow they had done their job they had a tone for the people's sin they understood the importance and the significance of that and in difficulty I would imagine they finished that job but they stopped a step short of true meaningful heartfelt worship because they understood God is absolutely concerned about us walking in obedience but not again that heartless obedience

30:48.546 --> 30:53.313
And the conundrum, by the way, of the entire Old Testament system is that it can be manipulated.

30:53.453 --> 30:54.414
It can be faked.

30:55.015 --> 30:58.880
And we as humans are so famous for looking for loopholes to exploit.

30:59.121 --> 31:07.172
I can just look this way on the outside and fake it before everybody else, when my heart is a hot mess, and God says, no, shut the gates.

31:07.613 --> 31:09.275
I want nothing to do with that.

31:10.737 --> 31:17.106
I would imagine you, like me, as you hear this story, you can think about similar times in your life.

31:17.730 --> 31:22.356
when your hands and your heart were not congruent.

31:22.376 --> 31:24.079
Times when maybe you were going through grief.

31:24.599 --> 31:25.841
You were going through suffering.

31:26.262 --> 31:28.404
And you knew things to be true about God.

31:28.464 --> 31:30.307
He's still God in your life.

31:30.768 --> 31:32.430
But you're not in a place of worship.

31:33.131 --> 31:37.817
You're not in a place expressing joy to him and happiness and delight.

31:37.977 --> 31:39.439
You're hurting and you're in pain.

31:40.160 --> 31:44.286
Maybe you're crying out for God to answer prayers that he just doesn't seem to be answering.

31:44.807 --> 31:47.410
Or he's answering him in a way that, Lord, that's not the answer I want.

31:47.714 --> 31:49.397
You're not behaving in a way that I want you to.

31:49.437 --> 31:50.639
It's just a struggle though.

31:50.659 --> 31:58.491
God, I know you're good and you're true and you're benevolent and you're sovereign, but God, I'm not there at a heart level right now.

31:58.511 --> 32:03.759
And to say those things, to sing those things would just be fake in those times.

32:03.799 --> 32:06.604
And sometimes what we do is we choose religion.

32:07.465 --> 32:09.348
And we fake it on the outside.

32:09.388 --> 32:13.114
We put up this external guise for everybody to see because it's just easier.

32:13.635 --> 32:15.538
It's easier than having to have the conversation.

32:15.874 --> 32:18.718
To show up at life group and say, this is how my life is wrecked this week.

32:18.738 --> 32:22.863
I'm struggling and I'm bitter and I'm angry on the inside and I'm off with God right now.

32:23.544 --> 32:26.829
To be like the psalmist word is brutally honest with God.

32:27.390 --> 32:29.292
They felt the freedom to be that by the way.

32:29.613 --> 32:31.916
To say what they felt because they knew God, you already know this.

32:32.537 --> 32:33.478
You know how I feel.

32:33.999 --> 32:34.900
You know I'm upset.

32:34.920 --> 32:35.601
You know I'm wrecked.

32:35.621 --> 32:36.622
You know that I love you.

32:36.662 --> 32:42.450
And I don't disagree with what your course of actions were, but God, this is really hard for me to swallow right now.

32:42.722 --> 32:47.954
And I am not in a place of delight and abundance and overwhelming joy.

32:47.994 --> 32:48.956
I'm just not there.

32:49.557 --> 32:55.089
So I'm not going to show up and fake it like I am because that's not what you want from me.

32:55.851 --> 32:58.156
That is not honoring to you.

32:59.239 --> 33:02.546
And why these two stories are here is they're meant to show us something.

33:03.266 --> 33:08.675
Leviticus 10, by the way, is only one of two narrative sections in the entire book of Leviticus.

33:09.076 --> 33:13.583
The whole rest of the book is about God's laws and sacrifice and how to obey those.

33:14.164 --> 33:19.132
And then you have this story that crops up in the middle of it and saying, this is what that looks like lived out.

33:19.874 --> 33:22.338
What is God's heart and desire regarding his law?

33:22.838 --> 33:27.767
Is it faithful, box checking, 100% of the time, obedience, regardless?

33:28.808 --> 33:29.810
Sure doesn't look that way.

33:30.210 --> 33:33.495
God is showing us that this is the true heart of a worshipper.

33:34.276 --> 33:38.421
That our heads and our heart and our hands are all connected.

33:39.042 --> 33:40.004
And Jesus would agree.

33:40.584 --> 33:44.330
He says on the Sermon in the Mount in Matthew chapter five, blessed are the poor in spirit.

33:44.770 --> 33:46.593
For theirs is the kingdom of heaven.

33:47.093 --> 33:49.076
The poor in spirit has the idea of bankrupt.

33:49.577 --> 33:52.661
How beautiful it is when we realize, Lord, we are bankrupt before you.

33:53.102 --> 33:54.123
We need you.

33:54.624 --> 33:56.146
This is the heart of the gospel.

33:56.546 --> 34:00.692
that for many of us in this room called us to him initially where we realized, Lord, I need you.

34:00.773 --> 34:01.994
I'm broken on the inside.

34:02.435 --> 34:06.001
My heart is wicked and it longs after things that aren't good for me.

34:06.501 --> 34:07.804
And I can't fix it.

34:08.445 --> 34:10.608
I need you to fix it for me.

34:11.429 --> 34:15.776
But it's that gospel that also tells us we need to continue to embrace that reality.

34:15.816 --> 34:17.459
God, I need to come back to you.

34:17.859 --> 34:24.850
I need to live whole before you in a meaningful way to remind myself that the work you started in me, you're good to finish.

34:25.122 --> 34:35.296
to remind ourselves that we are constantly in need of coming back to the God that saved us and to be honest, authentic people as we live before Him.

34:35.857 --> 34:36.718
We need Him.

34:37.499 --> 34:46.612
And this reality, by the way, is it lost on me knowing that we're heading into New Year's and many of us are thinking about resets and are eating in our exercise and a ton of other really good things.

34:46.732 --> 34:53.522
But all those things exist in kind of the do category, the box checking things and nothing again is wrong with those per se.

34:54.050 --> 35:00.319
But what God has truly after in our lives is not that, at least not that that's not connected to this.

35:01.301 --> 35:03.063
It's our hearts that He is after.

35:03.564 --> 35:06.188
It's our hearts He has always been after.

35:06.789 --> 35:20.850
So as you maybe ponder and reflect what God has for you in this new year, what He has for you in your daily worship of Him, would we too have the heart of Aaron in this, that recognizing in our brokenness that actually leads us to the Lord in authenticity

35:20.962 --> 35:22.103
honesty before him.

35:22.604 --> 35:30.133
And ultimately from that posture, we'll flow a right condition of our hands when our heart and our hands are connected.

35:31.254 --> 35:37.281
Father, thank you for these cherished stories in our Bible where we can see pictures of you that are so beautiful.

35:38.002 --> 35:44.690
Father, I pray that you would help us to understand the magnitude of this, the weight of this, and what you've done on our behalf.

35:44.898 --> 35:49.684
that you have made our hearts right through Christ and we can worship you in authenticity and in truth.

35:49.704 --> 36:00.076
And God, we have the freedom even on the hard days to admit where we are, to admit that we're broken, to admit that we're fragile and hurting in places of pain or admit that God, things are great and we love you.

36:00.116 --> 36:06.504
We're grateful for where you have us wherever that may be, but we can operate out of a true and authentic heart for you.

36:06.904 --> 36:07.445
God, thank you.

36:07.665 --> 36:11.049
Most of all for Christ, our risen Savior and whose name we pray.

36:11.490 --> 36:11.890
Amen.

